HEADWORD: Metronome
<hw>Met"ro*nome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ measure +
<?/ distribute, assign: cf. F. <ets>m⟦eacute⟧tronome</ets>, It.
<ets>metronomo</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument consisting of a short
pendulum with a sliding weight. It is set in motion by clockwork, and
serves to measure time in music.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

